description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/coap/coap_keys.c
Lines: 744-752

The CBOR decoder for PUT /keys/{iid} manually parses map header:
```c
if ((payload[0] & 0xe0) == 0xa0) {
    map_count = payload[0] & 0x1f;
} else if (payload[0] == 0xb8 && payload_len > 1) {
    map_count = payload[1];
} else {
    return -EINVAL;
}
```

This handles small maps (0xa0-0xb7) and 1-byte-length maps (0xb8 NN), but:
1. Does not handle 2-byte or 4-byte length maps (0xb9, 0xba)
2. Does not validate map_count against actual payload content
3. Indefinite-length maps (0xbf) are rejected (correct, but not documented)

If a client sends a well-formed map with >255 items or 2-byte length encoding, the request is incorrectly rejected.

Category: PROTOCOL - incomplete CBOR support
